The private sector, state officers and elected leaders will meet in Mombasa this week for talks on ensuring next year&rsquo;s August general elections is peaceful.A communication from the Kenya Private Sector Alliance informing MPs of the December 1-3 retreat arises from concerns that intensified campaigns and political tension could undermine investor confidence and threaten national security and stability.&ldquo;It allows leaders to share strategies on ensuring the 2017 general elections are not only peaceful, but also held in a manner that would guarantee national cohesion and unity for socioeconomic development,&rdquo; the letter reads.Agencies charged with overseeing elections, such as the IEBC, the Registrar of Political Parties, the Supreme Court and security agencies, will participate.